dct_description_sm: This line data layer represents contours for Portland Metro, Oregon in 1993. The dataset was originally published by the Metro Data Resource Center in February 2001.[Elevation lines from United States Geological Survey (USGS) 7.5 minute quadrangle maps. Contour interval is 10, 20 or 40 feet, depending on quad. As additional quads become available from USGS, the map extent will be expanded.]
